Used when the function uses `runTransaction` with complex ref-routing logic. Instead of using `createMockFirestore()`, these tests build the Firestore mock manually to control exactly which data is returned for each `transaction.get(ref)` call.

**Key technique -- `_type` tag on refs:**
```ts
const programRef = { id: PROGRAM_ID, _type: "program" };
const cardRef = { id: PROGRAM_ID, _type: "card" };
const txGet = jest.fn().mockImplementation((ref: any) => {
  if (ref._type === "program") return Promise.resolve(programSnap);
  if (ref._type === "card") return Promise.resolve(cardSnap);
  return Promise.resolve(createDocSnap(ref.id, undefined));
});
```

This is necessary because `addStamp` and `rewards` share the same document ID (`PROGRAM_ID`) but represent different Firestore paths. The `_type` tag disambiguates.

**Mock `runTransaction`:**
```ts
